---
Manage isolated workspaces for AI agents

Usage: aw <COMMAND>

Commands:
  init         Initialize base workspace (default: 'default')
  create       Create a new workspace from a base
  list         List all workspaces
  start        Enter workspace (tmux session if available)
  delete       Delete a workspace
  config       Show configuration file location
  edit-config  Open config file in default editor
  edit-base    Open base workspace directory in editor
  sync         Sync all repos in current workspace with remote
  reset        Reset all repos in current workspace to the remote default branch
  open-home    Open tool home directory in editor
  dash         Tmux-based dashboard for live agent state
  serve        Serve the phone remote-control web app over the LAN
  hook         Write an agent state transition (called by Claude/Codex/pi hooks)
  shell-init   Print shell hook for eval (e.g. `eval "$(aw shell-init zsh)"`)
  completions  Print shell completions
  install      Interactive setup helpers
  self         Self-management: check for updates, upgrade in place

Options:
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
